I answered that my firebolt of tallon with its 2K Dmage and 500 mana is better than Aegis of Ro and its 450 mana cost.  For this one to be better, mob need to hit more than 60 times in 8 minutes, and (happily) that's not true (if slowed).<br>
cadeau of flame with 155 mana only is much better, BUT tanks needs to ask (i am NOT going to put a timer)<br>
<br>
am I wrong ?<br>
(of course if DPS is needed, I can agree that Aegis is mandatory, as in trial for example).<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ikebana-toulouse.com/citation/signat.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khalendor>Khalendor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 142<br> <font color=#333333>(11/4/02 6:40:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1643.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DS or not DS that is the question</span><hr size=1> Yea, this is a valid question and I would like to hear others opinions.  Quite often if you are grouping with a shammy instead of a cleric, the shammy is slowing and healing so the mage is malosini, ds'g and nuking.  I don't mind ds'g if the tank wants it and it is going to be worthwhile.  With multiple mobs hitting the tank then obviously useful but with just one mob pulls what is the consensus?<br>
<br>
Oh, and I really wish there were a message that we got telling us that the ds has worn off.  I get tired of looking at my clock constantly when you have a tank that doesn't want to announce ds. <p>Khalendor Dayze</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xerphanis>Xerphanis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#333333>(11/4/02 8:06:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1643.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DS or not DS that is the question</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">How to get around Tanks that don't ask for refresh?</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
Until I got my Harnessed Flame Dirk, which casts Unity of Fire (35pt DS), I always did this...<br>
<br>
Have Shield of Fire (level 8 DS) and Cadeau of Flame memorized...<br>
<br>
Cast Shield of Fire on yourself, and Cadeau of Flame on the MT. Since the two DSs have comparable durations, you can use the cheaper DS as a timer for your more expensive DS.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Is it worth the mana?</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
Flamebolt of Talon does 1920 using 500 mana = 3.84 dmg/mana ratio...<br>
<br>
Combined, Shield of Flame and Cadeau of Flame is 190 mana used.<br>
<br>
Cadeau of Flame lasts 6.6 min at level 56 (so lowest duration assumed) and does 33dmg per hit.<br>
<br>
In order for DS to be &quot;worth it&quot;, it has to do 729.6dmg for the 190 mana that you've spent. At 33dmg per hit, as long as the MT gets hit 22.11 every 6.6min, then the DS would be worth it.<br>
<br>
If the MT gets hit for more than 22.11 times, which happens frequently, then you're already being more efficient than Firebolt.<br>
<br>
Aegis of Ro is for lazy people that don't want to keep track of DSs~ The only times I've personally used it is for raid mobs that require high FR, since DS FR stacks with mostly everything.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps, <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mitglied.lycos.de/sirnamib/hpbimg/xerph.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->[64 Arch Mage] <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60465" target="top">Xerphanis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Officer of &lt; <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.monkeyo.org/enshadowed" target="top">Enshadowed</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> &gt;</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hydronium>hydronium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(11/4/02 8:14:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1643.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://ourworld.cs.com/biospiral23/Face1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DS or not DS that is the question</span><hr size=1> Perhaps DS is not mana effecient at dealing damage.. but have you ever thought that the people in your group l0v3 you that much more because they have some cool sounding DS buff on them? Sometimes, just because it's fun.. I think you should do it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://ourworld.cs.com/biospiral23/Badhydro.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
