<br>
If there is a shaman slowing though, I will often not bother with a DS.  It just doesn't seem worth it with the mob swinging about once a game day. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   There are only 3 times I can think of that I DS with a shaman around.<br>
<br>
1. Raid mobs that will take some noticable time to get slowed, or moderately long fights.<br>
<br>
2. Unslowable mobs (even in xp groups, things like Archaic Models in PoI are unslowable).<br>
<br>
3. Slow puller and I am in danger of hitting full mana. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103898" target="top">Baron Evelle Fyrestrike</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
