/cast 2 &lt;-- 2 being where Cadeau is memmed<br>
/pause 386000 &lt;--- 386 sec for 6.6 mins 1000 = 1 sec<br>
/g Cadeau of Flames has worn off.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->You realise this disables your ability to use any other hotkey for the duration of the pause, right?  6.6 minutes is a LONG time not to be able to use any of your other hotkeys.<br>
<br>
On the issue at hand, personally I say teach the tank to type '/g DS' when it wears off.  It's not too taxing on them, and it makes the process much easier.  <br>
<br>
Also, mention to them that while they're standing there whacking the mob, you're busy controlling your pet, nuking, summoning items for others, and trying to manage aggro, so typing &quot;I SAID DS&quot; 10 seconds after the initial request ain't gonna help their cause. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   You'll get to them in time. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style=""><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59365">Kathodos</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Battle Cleric of Tunare - Tholuxe Paells</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style=""><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59365">Kantreach</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Arch Mage Antagonist - Tholuxe Paells</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=erun>Erun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#333333>(11/5/02 2:08:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1643.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: comment</span><hr size=1> There are custom UI files that will add a small timer to your interface.<br>
<br>
I've used this for DS timing as well as the 5 min modrod refresh timing.  It really works nicely.<br>
<br>
The downside is that often these custom files are incompatible with EQ immediately after patching, so you have to disable them until the developers modify them to be compatible again.<br>
<br>
